---
// Why Nothing's Worked Section - Pattern Recognition
---

<section id="why-nothings-worked" class="bg-brand-gray py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-24">
  <div class="section-container">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12 sm:mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-text mb-4">
          You've tried before. Here's why it didn't work.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-brand-muted">
          It's not willpower. It's one of three patterns.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pattern Cards -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">

        <!-- Pattern 1: The Motion Guy -->
        <div class="pattern-card bg-brand-dark p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-accent/20 hover:border-brand-accent cursor-pointer transition-all" data-pattern="motion">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-text mb-2">The Motion Guy</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm mb-4">"I'm training but nothing's changing"</p>
          <div class="pattern-preview">
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">
              You show up. Three, four times a week. Mirror hasn't changed in months.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pattern-expanded hidden mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-brand-accent/20">
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              You've tried different programs, different splits, more volume.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              You're not lazy. You're grinding. But effort without feedback just burns you out faster.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-text font-semibold">
              You're in motion. But nothing's actually moving.
            </p>
          </div>
          <button class="expand-btn text-brand-accent text-sm mt-4 hover:underline">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 2: The Monday-Thursday Guy -->
        <div class="pattern-card bg-brand-dark p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-accent/20 hover:border-brand-accent cursor-pointer transition-all" data-pattern="monday">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-text mb-2">The Monday-Thursday Guy</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm mb-4">"I start strong but collapse by the weekend"</p>
          <div class="pattern-preview">
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">
              You start every week dialled. By Thursday you're just reacting.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pattern-expanded hidden mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-brand-accent/20">
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              Gym before work. Meals prepped. Locked in. Then a client melts down. A deal goes sideways. The week piles up.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              By Thursday you're not making choices anymore. You're just reacting.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-text font-semibold">
              Weekend reset. Monday restart. Same loop for years.
            </p>
          </div>
          <button class="expand-btn text-brand-accent text-sm mt-4 hover:underline">Read more</button>
        </div>

        <!-- Pattern 3: The Empty Tank Guy -->
        <div class="pattern-card bg-brand-dark p-6 rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-accent/20 hover:border-brand-accent cursor-pointer transition-all" data-pattern="empty">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-text mb-2">The Empty Tank Guy</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm mb-4">"I'm showing up but I've got nothing left"</p>
          <div class="pattern-preview">
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">
              You drag yourself to the gym because you're supposed to.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pattern-expanded hidden mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-brand-accent/20">
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              Weights feel heavier than they should. Energy isn't there. Results definitely aren't.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted mb-3">
              You keep showing up because that's what you do. Push through. Grind it out.
            </p>
            <p class="text-brand-text font-semibold">
              But you're stacking workouts on top of a system that's already depleted. More effort just digs the hole deeper.
            </p>
          </div>
          <button class="expand-btn text-brand-accent text-sm mt-4 hover:underline">Read more</button>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Transition Block -->
      <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <p class="text-xl text-brand-text mb-4">Which one sounds familiar?</p>
        <p class="text-brand-muted mb-4">
          Different patterns. Same root cause.
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-muted mb-4">
          Your system is underpowered. You've been trying to build on an empty tank.
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-text font-semibold text-lg">
          More willpower won't fix it. Another program won't fix it. You need a system built for how your brain actually works when you're running a business.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Bridge -->
      <div class="bg-brand-dark p-8 sm:p-10 rounded-lg border border-brand-accent/30">
        <h3 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-text mb-6 text-center">
          Why This System Works
        </h3>

        <p class="text-brand-muted text-center mb-8">
          Meals planned. Workouts programmed. Daily check-ins. This isn't random. It's designed for the three patterns that kill consistency.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold mb-2">For the Motion Guy</p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">Daily check-ins make progress visible. Your brain starts believing effort matters again.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold mb-2">For the Monday-Thursday Guy</p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">No decisions to make when your tank is empty. Meals are done. Workouts are loaded. You just execute.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-brand-accent font-semibold mb-2">For the Empty Tank Guy</p>
            <p class="text-brand-muted text-sm">Recovery is built in, not earned. Training that adds to your body instead of draining what's left.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl text-brand-text font-semibold text-center">
          Your willpower stops being the bottleneck.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <p class="text-brand-muted mb-4">Ready to fix what's actually broken?</p>
        <button
          class="btn-primary text-lg py-4 px-10"
          onclick="window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('daisy:open'))"
        >
          Apply Now
        </button>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // Pattern card expand/collapse
  document.querySelectorAll('.pattern-card').forEach(card => {
    const expandBtn = card.querySelector('.expand-btn');
    const expanded = card.querySelector('.pattern-expanded');
    const preview = card.querySelector('.pattern-preview');

    if (expandBtn && expanded && preview) {
      expandBtn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
        e.stopPropagation();
        const isHidden = expanded.classList.contains('hidden');

        if (isHidden) {
          expanded.classList.remove('hidden');
          preview.classList.add('hidden');
          expandBtn.textContent = 'Show less';
          card.classList.add('border-brand-accent');
        } else {
          expanded.classList.add('hidden');
          preview.classList.remove('hidden');
          expandBtn.textContent = 'Read more';
          card.classList.remove('border-brand-accent');
        }
      });
    }
  });
</script>
